# CLAUDE.local.md (template)

> Rename this file to `CLAUDE.local.md` to activate it.
> The actual `CLAUDE.local.md` is in `.gitignore`, so personal preferences stay personal.

Personal overrides loaded only for you. Examples below, delete what does not apply.

## Communication style

- Respond in: (your preferred language)
- Tone: (e.g., direct and firm, conversational, formal)
- Avoid: (e.g., em-dashes, hedging language)
- Confirm before: (e.g., changing locked dates, deleting files)

## Local environment

- Node version: (e.g., 22 LTS via nvm)
- Database port: (e.g., 5432, 5433 for local)
- Other local services and ports

## Shortcuts and aliases

- (e.g., "when I say 'the spec', I mean specs/<latest>/spec.md")
- (e.g., "always use pnpm, never npm or yarn")

## Notes

Anything else you want Claude to remember about how you work, that is not relevant to the rest of the team.
